## Billing address

The following HTTP GET request

<pre class="terminal">
https://www.<%= settings.domain %>/oauth2/address?oauth_token=124fFAGRNJru1FTz70BzhT3Zg...
</pre>

returns user's billing address in [JSON](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JSON)
format:

<pre class="terminal">
$ curl https://www.<%= settings.domain %>/oauth2/address?oauth_token=124fFAGRNJru1FTz70BzhT3Zg...
</pre>

~~~ javascript
{
  "first_name":"Τάσος",
  "last_name":"Τασάκης",
  "email":"home@example.com",
  "mobile":"6971234567",
  "phone":"2101234567",
  "address":"Πάρου 34",
  "zip":"17234",
  "city":"Αθήνα",
  "region":"Αττικής",
  "street_name":"Πάρου",
  "street_number":"34",
  "invoice":false,
  "company":"",
  "doy":"",
  "afm":"",
  "profession":"",
  "company_phone":""
}
~~~

Τhe address resource supports [JSONP](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JSONP). Once
you complete the required server-side steps, you can expose the `oauth_token` at
client side. Then, with JavaScript and [XHR](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XMLHttpRequest)
retrieve user's address and pre-fill the form.

To get the billing address of a user in [JSONP](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JSONP)
format, you have to set the `callback` parameter with the function name (e.g. `aFunction`)
you want to be invoked.

**Example:**

<pre class="terminal">
$ curl https://www.<%= settings.domain %>/oauth2/address?callback=aFunction&oauth_token=124fFAGRNJru1FTz70BzhT3Zg...
</pre>

~~~ javascript
aFunction({
  "first_name":"Τάσος",
  "last_name":"Τασάκης",
  "email":"home@example.com"
    ...
})
~~~

## Shipping address

In case shipping address is different from billing address, it will be present at
the entity `shipping_address`. For example:

~~~ javascript
{
  "first_name":"Τάσος",
  "last_name":"Τασάκης",
  "email":"home@example.com",
  "mobile":"6971234567",
  "phone":"2101234567",
  "address":"Πάρου 34",
  "zip":"17234",
  "city":"Αθήνα",
  "region":"Αττικής",
  "street_name":"Πάρου",
  "street_number":"34",
  "invoice":false,
  "company":"",
  "doy":"",
  "afm":"",
  "profession":"",
  "company_phone":"",
  "shipping_address":{
    "first_name":"Τάσος",
    "last_name":"Τασάκης",
    "mobile":"",
    "phone":"2101234567",
    "address":"Σύρου 12",
    "zip":"18151",
    "city":"Αθήνα",
    "region":"Αττικής"
    "street_name":"Σύρου",
    "street_number":"12"
  }
}
~~~

## Invoice

If user requested invoice, then the `invoice` entity will be `true` and the
relevant entities (`company`, `doy`, `afm`, `profession`, `company_phone`) will
be filled with the information.

~~~ javascript
{
  "first_name":"Τάσος",
  "last_name":"Τασάκης",
  "email":"home@example.com",
  "mobile":"6971234567",
  "phone":"2101234567",
  "address":"Πάρου 34",
  "zip":"17234",
  "city":"Αθήνα",
  "region":"Αττικής",
  "street_name":"Πάρου",
  "street_number":"34",
  "invoice":true,
  "company":"Skroutz",
  "doy":"Α Αθηνων",
  "afm":"123456789",
  "profession":"Engineer",
  "company_phone":"2101234567"
}
~~~

